<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1900-09-16T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1900-09-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="77" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d77">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">President of Chile</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">President of the United
                            States</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Translation.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Santiago, Chile</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1900-09-16"><hi rend="italic">September 16, 1900</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>The President of Chile, deeply moved by the catastrophe of Galveston,
                            shares, with all his heart, the sorrow of your country.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Federico
                            Errazuriz.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>